        content: "N+1 PROBLEM — capcana clasică ORM:\n```php\n<?php\n// GREȘIT — N+1 queries:\n$users = User::all(); // 1 query\nforeach ($users as $user) {\n    echo $user->profil->bio; // 1 query PER user! = N+1 total\n}\n// 100 useri = 101 queries → lent\n\n// CORECT — Eager Loading cu WITH:\n$users = User::with('profil')->get(); // 2 queries totale (users + profiles)\n$users = User::with(['profil', 'comenzi'])->get(); // 3 queries\n\n// Nested eager loading:\n$users = User::with('comenzi.produse')->get();\n```\n\nSCOPES — filtre reutilizabile în Model:\n```php\n<?php\nclass User extends Model {\n    // Local scope:\n    public function scopeActivi($query) {\n        return $query->where('activ', true);\n    }\n    public function scopeAdmin($query) {\n        return $query->where('role', 'admin');\n    }\n}\n\n// Utilizare (fără 'scope' prefix, fluent):\n$activi = User::activi()->get();\n$adminActivi = User::activi()->admin()->get();\n```\n\nQUERY BUILDER (fara ORM):\n```php\n<?php\nuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\DB;\n\n$users = DB::table('users')\n    ->select('id', 'name', 'email')\n    ->where('activ', 1)\n    ->where('varsta', '>', 18)\n    ->orWhere('role', 'admin')\n    ->orderBy('name')\n    ->limit(10)\n    ->offset(20)\n    ->get();\n\n// RAW expressions pentru performanță:\n$stats = DB::table('comenzi')\n    ->select(DB::raw('DATE(created_at) as data'), DB::raw('COUNT(*) as total'))\n    ->groupBy('data')\n    ->orderByDesc('data')\n    ->limit(30)\n    ->get();\n```\n\nLA INTERVIU: Când folosești Eloquent vs Query Builder? Eloquent pentru CRUD, relații, validare. Query Builder pentru rapoarte complexe, GROUP BY, statistici — mai performant.",
